Description: Label of the allele
Overall number of sequences assigned to this allele
For inferred alleles, the closest reference gene and allele
For inferred alleles, the closest reference gene and allele that is in the subject's inferred genotype
For inferred alleles, the number of nucleotides that differ between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele
For inferred alleles, the number of nucleotides that differ between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele that is in the subject's inferred genotype
For inferred alleles,  comma-separated list of nucleotide substitutions (e.g. G112A) between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele (using IMGT-gapped sequences for V-genes).
For inferred alleles, the number of amino acids that differ between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele
For inferred alleles, the list of amino acid substitutions (e.g. A96N) between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele (using IMGT-gapped sequences for V-genes).
The number of sequences exactly matching this unmutated sequence
The number of sequences exactly matching this allele divided by the number of sequences assigned to this allele, x 100
The number of molecules (identified by Unique Molecular Identifiers) exactly matching this unmutated sequence (if UMIs were used)
The number of sequences exactly matching the sequence of this allele divided by the number of sequences exactly matching any allele of this specific gene, x 100
The number of sequences exactly matching this sequence divided by the number of sequences exactly matching any allele of any gene, x 100
The number of V allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) found associated with this allele
The number of D allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) found associated with this allele
The number of J allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) found associated with this allele
The number of unique CDR3s found associated with this allele
The number of V allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) associated with unmutated sequences of this allele
The number of D allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) associated with unmutated sequences of this allele
The number of J allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) associated with unmutated sequences of this allele
The number of unique CDR3s associated with unmutated sequences of this allele
The locus (or loci) from which haplotyping was inferred (e.g. IGHJ6)
The ratio (expressed as two percentages) with which the two inferred haplotypes were found (e.g. 60:40)
The consensus sequence provided by the inference tool
